"Best Western hotel"

   [blank.png] 2
   User
   13/08/2018

   The reception staff never seemed interested in me when I spoke with
   them... when I checked out the man and lady spoke french all the time
   even though they knew I was English. The breakfast was a real
   disappointment and there was no restaurant all weekend. This was not
   mentioned when I booked. The pool area is small and not enough sun
   beds. The service behind the bar was questionable and the first beer
   served to me was off and I had to explain to the barman that the beer
   was off. Overall very disappointed with the hotel, the only saving
   grace was the room was nice and it is within walking distance of the
   centre. However I stay alot with the best western group but will not be
   returning to this hotel.

   Hotel-Le-Galice, Responsable relations clients at Best Western Le
   Galice Centre-Ville, responded to this review
   Dear customer, Thank you for your feedback. We are sorry to hear that
   the checkout didn't go well and the breakfast disappointed you even if
   we propose a large choice of meal as fruits, viennoiseries, fresh
   handmade juices... Due to a technical issue we couldn't open the
   restaurant for a week, we are also sorry that it happened during your
   stay. We hope to see you come back in our hotel to prove you this case
   was exceptional. Have a nice day, Loïc - communication manager

