   set just right. The walk-in shower was spacious. The contemporary
   reception area was welcoming. Check out the amazing artwork. I wish we
   could have stayed long enough to go swimming.Breakfast was great.

   Hotel-Le-Galice, Responsable relations clients at Best Western Le
   Galice Centre-Ville, responded to this review
   Dear customer, Thank you for your feedback. We are glad to hear that
   your stay was good and that you discovered our beautiful city by our
   side. We won't forget to tell our teams that you noticed their
   professionnalism concerning the cleaning and the reception. We hope to
   see you back soon in our hotel Best Western Le Galice in Aix en
   Provence. Have a nice day, Loïc - communication manager

"Not bad but outside city walls. Avoid in Summer"

   [blank.png] 3
   User
   26/07/2018

   Nice breakfast buffet. One is unable to control Air conditioning in
   very hot July weather and room way too hot at their lowest central
   setting. Avoid in Summer. 15 minutes walk to the main part of town. 6
