   bar had a great hamburger, as per my travel companion.

"Nice sized rooms, excellent customer service"

   [blank.png] 4
   Drey98, New Jersey
   25/07/2018

   The BW Le Galice was a hotel used by my group tour. As others have
   mentioned, it is a 20 minute walk from the center of town but it is
   easy to walk there and convenient to the huge Casino grocery store. The
   hotel seems understaffed but the one male representative was very
   helpful. He was personally coming up to my room to help me use the
   safe, turn on the air conditioning, etc. when he could have sent a tech
   person up. The bar area was nice and we watched the World Cup on the
   big screen TV.

"Great stay a few minutes walk from center of town."

   [blank.png] 5
   albert501, Toronto, Canada
   19/07/2018

   Great location , staff was very nice and helpful. Room was spacious ,
   clean bed comfortable. Fridge in the room helped. Complimentary bottles
   of water were really helpful. Swimming pool with bar was very nice to
   use. Inside parking was good. Location was excellent. Overall a very
   positive stay. If i had a suggestion, it would be the signage to find
   the hotel the first time, that was challenging as it is in a side
   street and it is hard to see the sign from the main street.

"Ok for work, but a bit off"

   [blank.png] 3
   Break12, Stockholm, Sweden
   11/07/2018

   About 15 min walk to Aix center. Located a bit off, behind car sale
   places. Ok modern standard rooms, good breakfast and ok pool. Overall
   ok, but nothing special. A bit unknowledgeable staff, they could not
   advise on transport to Cannes, and didn't know which station the buses
   leave from. (For those wondering, Flixbus from Aix to Cannes and Nice
   Airport leaves from the station at Krypton, Avenue de l'Arc de Meyran)

"Perfect!"

   [blank.png] 5
   Mantalope, Augusta, Georgia
   08/07/2018

   Don't be fooled by the Best Western chain hotel stigma. This is a very
   nice hotel, and in no way resembles a chain hotel except, I must say in
   the best ways...clean fresh towels daily, air conditioning, king size
   bed, awesome pool, WiFi, and a huge flat screen in your room. A little
   off putting when you drive up because it is located between multiple
   car dealerships, but get over that. Parking is under the hotel, and
   secure. It is a solid 20 minute walk to the town center, but safe. We
   took a cab several times (7 euro) to the center just to save time. The
   staff was over the top in every way, very helpful and friendly. Your
   only hesitation may be the distance to town, if you have walking issues
   ,or telling your friends you went to Aix and stayed in a Best Western!
   However, there is nothing better than coming back to this hotel after a
   long day of local or regional touring. In July, an air conditioned
   room, a dip in the fantastic refreshing pool, and a nice bottle of rose
   at the poolside bar gets you ready for the next days adventure. We
   would come back with no hesitation.

"Aix"

   [blank.png] 4
