"Adequate for our needs"

   [blank.png] 3
   Eric G, WAshington, DC
   25/09/2017

   We stayed for 4 nights in late July, and while it wasn't flashy, it was
   good for what we needed. The rooms and baths look recently remodeled,
   if the decor is a bit basic. The bed was really comfortable, and the
   bath was roomy with a good deep tub. The breakfast was nice, though the
   coffee machines were a bit of a surprise. The coffee was fine. The area
   around the hotel isn't much to talk about, but there is a nice cafe and
   bakery around the corner, and a grocery store about 5 minutes away. The
   walk into town is about 15-20 minutes but easy, and shaded in the
   morning and later in the afternoon. There was plenty of parking in the
   garage. My father had a leaking AC unit in his room and once he alerted
   them they had him in a new room within an hour. We don't really have
   any complaints about our stay. Its not the flashiest hotel, but for us,
   out and about for most of the day, it did the job.

"Business trip"

   [blank.png] 2
   DavidCabot, Portishead, United Kingdom
   18/09/2017

   Very tired and dreary hotel. The rooms were kept clean but the common
   areas are awful. Needs a complete overhaul. If you just want somewhere
   inexpensive to sleep it will suffice. The bar was out of beer for
   several days.

"Very helpful and attentive staff"

   [blank.png] 4
   wendygp, Plymouth, United Kingdom
   14/09/2017

   A quick check-in with a small coach party, cases came up very promptly.
   A lovely large room with a safe, TV, T/C, fridge, plenty of hangers,
   not much shelving to put things on or cupboards. A lovely firm bed,
   good lighting and mirrors. Air con VG. The bathroom had a bath/shower.
   No slip mats but told to use a towel, a separate bidet and loo. Liquid
   soap and lovely large thick towels. We stayed for 3 nights and had
   dinner in for 2 of them. The 2nd night we had Lucas and Lionel serving
   us, plus another party of about 20+. These two young men were amazing
   running about with food and drinks. No one was kept waiting, they were
   amazing. I was impressed. This was served outside by the pool. The pool
   area not large, but the pool a good size, towels provided if requested.
   BF a good variety of fresh fruit, yogurt and breads. I loved the dining
   room decoration of large chandeliers and one wall had 3 large paintings
   of French ladies dancing. Table clearing tended to be a bit slow and
   the tables are not very large. Dietary needs taken care of . Near a
   rail line, but l didn't hear any trains. The hotel is about 15 min's
   walk to the centre of town, on Thursdays they have a street market.
   Also a Noddy train which l used, to see more of the area. Enjoyed my
   stay.

"standard hotel not far from downtown Aix en Provence."

   [blank.png] 3
   User
   09/08/2017

   the hotel is standard BW nothing special. During my stay it was full of
   young soccer players and it was a little bit noisy. Breakfast was good.
   It's not far from downtown along a traffic avenue. I arrived in the
