   Hotel-Le-Galice, Responsable commercial at Best Western Hotel le
   Galice, responded to this review
   Dear Leonardo, I would like to thank you for taking some time to share
   your experience in our hotel. I'm pleased that you enjoyed our buffet
   breakfast and our central location in town. Indeed, our rooms are
   guarantied for 4 p.m. You are able as well to leave some suitcases in
   our luggage room if needed. I am sorry that the soccer players welcomed
   in our hotel the same night as yours could have been a little bit
   noisy. Please be sure that your comfort and well being is our priority
   in the Best Western Hotel le Galice. Looking forward to welcome you
   again in Provence Best regards Justine LAISSUS, sales manager

"Tired rooms & poor location."

   [blank.png] 3
   TopsMA, Den Bosch, The Netherlands
   28/06/2017

   The location of the hotel is less than perfect but they were honest
   about the distance to downtown Aix & when you are at home booking, a
   15-20 minute walk sounds fine..... it's when you have to walk it four
   times in the day (one trip, there & back, to explore & second trip,
   there & back, for dinner) in temperatures of 34C that it seems like a
   very BAD idea! We had a car, but given that the hotel offers parking
   and the idea of trying to find parking in town was not appealing, we
   chose to walk. The area where the hotel is situated is also not
   attractive, has no restaurants or stores close by, other than a gas
   station. Maybe the hotel could offer transport to the town centre as
   I'm sure it's older guests find that walk next to impossible in that
   heat! The room was spacious with aircon but very tired (our wardrobe
   doors had been removed & the bare rough edges of the frame just left
   exposed). Breakfast was good -typical and plentiful. The staff were
   friendly'ish, but not charming and were a little standoffish at times.
   Generally the hotel seemed tired and dreary, the location poor and when
   I visit Aix again I'm afraid this will not be my first choice of hotel.

"Helpful staff"

   [blank.png] 4
   CT_FB, Toronto
   19/05/2017

   We arrived from the airport by express bus and couldn't find a taxi to
   the hotel. They sent a cab to collect us so we didn't have to struggle
   with our luggage. Reception had several other guests, but always
   managed to remain calm and helpful. We like being a little away from
   the noise - but delighted to walk into the centre for dinner.

"Sad, dreary and not worth it"

   [blank.png] 1
   Lillyput918, Milan, Italy
   15/11/2016

   So many things are just wrong about this hotel. The lobby area is ok
   but that's the only good thing I can say about this hotel. Our room was
   dark and dreary. Everything was brown and the poor lighting in the room
   didn't help. It was clean. When we arrived we were told the restaurant
   was closed. There was no mention of this on the website. So, after a
   long day of driving we had to head out to find something to eat. We
   ended up at McDonald's as most restaurants were closed. Back at the
   hotel the front desk personnel were often MIA. The parking garage was a
   nightmare that we paid an extra 15 euros for. The breakfast was so bad.
   The scrambled eggs tasted like water and again this was an extra cost
   of 12,50 each. I could go on and on about this terrible hotel but I'll
   just end it here by recommending that you find another hotel for your
   stay in Aix-en-Provence.

   Hotel-Le-Galice, Responsable commercial at Best Western Hotel le
   Galice, responded to this review
   Dear Guest, Thank you for your comment, however I think there is a
   mistake about our establishment. We do not have a parking for 15 €, our
   breakfast is not 12.50 € either and the closing of our restaurant is
   mentioned on all communication media, but we have room service
   available 24h / 24 and 7/7. So I think you're making a mistake about
   the establishment. Thank you for doing the necessary to remove this
   comment that does not concern our establishment. Best regards, Benjamin
   Orthis Sales manager

