"Oh dear, of dear, only if you have to..."

   [blank.png] 1
   budgetfussy, London
   09/07/2016

   We stayed here for three nights. It was one of the few hotels in Aix
   with a pool, that was reasonably affordable and not in the middle of
   nowhere. All other hotels near the centre with pools were very
   expensive. Yet, I did not quite expect such a fiasco. We were allocated
   a room with a view over the car park. I went bak to reception to state
   that we paid extra for a poolside room. The lady said that is not what
   her booking form said. My reply was that it was not my problem, but
   that we specifically paid more. Reluctantly they moved us to a room
   overlooking the pool(view massively overrated). Anyway, when I got back
   with the new key card, it didn't work, so I had to traipse back to
   reception again. Our original requests to have two key cards, which is
   generally the norm everywhere in the world if you are two guests, were
   denied. The reason for only one key card was that they didn't have any
   more....... (one can generally buy these key cards 500 to a box, and
   they certainly don't have 500 rooms) The reception staff was poor from
   start to finish. As it was extremely hot, I went to ask for an extra
   bed sheet, as the duvet in the room would have been too hot. I was
   told, "NO BED SHEET", just like that. I was surprised, as I didn't
   think it was a huge request. Eventually the lady on reception wrote my
   room number down with a huge sigh. They then brought it. It turned out
   to be a duvet cover. So again I had to go and explain that it was too
   hot for a duvet, and that I would an extra bed sheet to sleep under.
   They could not understand by I didn't want a duvet cover. Only then did
   they bring the correct item. When going to reception on several
   occasions, there wold be no one there, and the reception staff could be
   heard chatting in the back office. Several times some French guests
   would shout at the closed door, and then the staff would appear with no
   apology whatsoever. The second day, after a long day, we got to the
   room, and again the key card did not work. By now it was getting a bit
   long in the tooth. The second last day I was using the pool in the
   morning. The toilet by the pool and outside restaurant was out of
   order, and the sign said to use the lobby toilets. When then going to
   the lobby toilets, it had no toilet paper. This is just poor. First of
   all, all their conference rooms were booked, so the lobby toilets would
   get used a lot more. But the fact is that almost any hotel in the world
   has an hourly toilet check for lobby toilets, to make sure they are
   stocked and cleaned. Here, they just don't care. So again, I had to
   speak to reception to tell them there is no toilet paper. The bathroom
   in our room(406) had these big dirty marks on it, with some of the
   tiles white, and the others grey with dirt. It seriously needed a good
   deck scrubber. The only good things about this hotel is the comfortable
   beds, and the pool. As it gets extremely hot in Provence in the summer,
   a cooling dip in the pool after a hot day was very nice. But that's
   about it. The pictures of the rooms on booking sites are not accurate,
   as we had furniture that looked straight from the seventies in our
   room. If this hotel just gets the basics right, and teach the staff the
   basics in customer services and manners, they will make a lot of
   progress. If in Aix at any different time of year, I would certainly
   not stay here. There is a lot of hotels closer to town. The wifi was
   free, but one had to sign in again every 3 hours. Also, it did NOT
   allow apps like whatsapp to work, which it very poor. They probably
   don't care much about normal guests, as it seemed they do a lot of
   business with tour groups staying one night at a time, and their
   conference rooms.

   Hotel-Le-Galice, Responsable commercial at Best Western Hotel le
   Galice, responded to this review
   Good evening, We would like to thank you for helping us improve the
   quality of our Hotel and we are genuinely sorry to hear about your
   disappointment regarding your experience. So many unfortunate
   accidents! I guarantee you that today's team are working hard to
   strengthen and develop a unique guests experience based on respect,
   friendliness and attention to details. I would like to thank you again
   for your constructive feedback, and we hope that we will be able to
   count on you in the next coming years. I hope you let us a second
   chance and that we would have the privilege to welcome you again at the
   Hotel Le Galice! Kind regards, Benjamin Orthis Sales manager

"Could do better"

   [blank.png] 3
   NickKhobar, Al Khobar
   07/07/2016

   The good: clean, basic room. Comfortable bed with nice pillows.
   Pleasant staff. Reasonable breakfast. 24 hour restaurant. Swimming
   pool. Secure underground parking. 10 minutes walk from town. The not so
   good:slow internet that times out and drops out frequently. Can't Skype
   or FaceTime on the free internet - you have to pay €6 for that. Liquid
   soap attached to the wall. €12 breakfast not value for money. €13 for
   underground parking for a motorcycle - seriously?!? Overpriced. I'd
   look elsewhere next time, I was disappointed.

"Comfortable for the price, but a bit far out of town"

   [blank.png] 3
   User
   29/06/2016

   We stayed in this hotel a night during our stay in Aix-en-Provence. The
   hotel is large and has a bar and dinner area. The check in was
   efficient and quick and they had a place for us to keep our luggage
   before check in (4pm?!). We parked downstairs in their private parking
   area, which is nice that is covered, but a quite tight space. Parking
   at 14 EUR extra. The room was ok - as your would expect from a 3-star
   hotel. Shampoo was available, for example. The shame about the hotel is
   that is a bit of walk to the downtown and the area walking to downtown
   is not the best..or did not feel like it when we did it. I would agree
   with comments that it looks a bit run down, but then again, you get
   what you pay for.

   Hotel-Le-Galice, Responsable commercial at BEST WESTERN Hotel le
   Galice, responded to this review
   Dear Brian, First of all I would like to thank you so much for taking
   the time to share your comments on TripAdvisor regarding your recent
   stay at Le Galice. I would like to assure you that we constantly strive
   to achieve only the highest level of quality, service and hospitality
   and I truly regret that we fell short on our goals during your latest
   trip to Aix-en-Provence staying with us. I would like to extend my most
   sincere apologizes. Kind regards, Benjamin Orthis Sales Manager

