"Not a business hotel"

   [blank.png] 2
   User
   18/03/2016

   This hotel has tiny rooms with no amenities. The internet logs off
   every hour and the login is so complicated that it is very frustrating.
   The hotel does not provide any toilet amenities and the service is
   quite pathetic. Not a business friendly hotel. In my group of 6 people,
   the hotel messed up the booking and denied rooms to 4 people. Avoid and
   I am sure there are better hotels in aix en provence

   Hotel-Le-Galice, Directeur général at BEST WESTERN Hotel le Galice,
   responded to this review
   Hello sir, Thank you for your review of our hotel. Unfortunately I
   think this does not apply to our hotel. Indeed our rooms are a minimum
   of 25M, which is well above the standards 3 stars. We have toilet and
   shower in every room, otherwise we could not be referenced Best Western
   Core. On the internet, we have installed fiber optics to a rate of up
   to 100Mb / s. I really do not understand your comment and let you get
   back to me with your bill, so make sure that you have stayed in our
   hotel. Best regards

"Nice hotel"

   [blank.png] 4
   User
   08/03/2016

   We stayed at Hotel le Galice for 5 days after our car broke down on the
   way home from a weeks holiday with our two children in Cannes. The
   staff were extremely helpfull and kind. If I were to mention anything
   negative it is that the hotel is about a 15 minute walk from the center
   of Aix, wich seemed very far in the scorching July heat (about 35-38
   degrees celcius). But i would absolutely stay at the hotel again.

"A bit far from the city center "

