   a fact.

"BW Hotel le Galice"

   [blank.png] 3
   Ron S, New York City, New York
   02/02/2016

   It was alright for an overnight stay as the front desk staff were nice
   and helpful but the internet policy of the hotel leaves much more to be
   desired as they provide free Wi-Fi for general surfing but charge for
   accessing applications. It's no big deal to pay €6 per device if you
   really need it but it's not good practice. They have a parking garage
   at €14 per night but you can park on the street in front of the hotel
   or at the parking lot behind it until 8 am for free. They charge €12 (I
   think) for breakfast but we didn't buy it. The room was clean and quiet
   but the bathroom was outdated with spots of mold around the bathtub
   (see the pics). The location is close to the city center and not far
   from the highway.

