"Hotel just ok to spend the night"

   [blank.png] 3
   Robert D, Cologne, Germany
   25/09/2015

   We stayed 2 days in AIx to explore the City. We have choosen the Best
   Western Hotel because of its location nearby the centre (15 minutes
   walk) and parking facilities. Room was ok, the bed was ok, but
   everything was a littlebit worn out and the service was average. We
   only took breakfast the first morning since we found out that was
   offered was no value for money. Also not very good Service, e.g. no
   plates availabe, had to search myselve for a plate or the warm dish
   (scrambled eggs?) served cold.

"Air conditioning = open your window"

   [blank.png] 1
   Jbath, Bishop, Georgia
   24/09/2015

   We came with a group of 50 people, which would fill about a third of
   hotel's rooms. We noticed the room was warm and the air conditioning
   was no longer working. We called reception about the problem. We were
   told Management "decided" that all hotel rooms would have to do without
   room air conditioning, because too many rooms chose to open their one
   slightly openable window; the air conditioning system was not broken,
   it was just decided by management that there would be only "fresh air"
   offered, via the window..........we wanted to talk to someone in
   management, but were told that they were gone for the day and would not
   be reachable..........we were stunned ......... It felt like a Seinfeld
   episode. Instead the "Soup Nazi" it was the "Air conditioning Nazi".
   "NO AC FOR YOU TODAY !" ........We paid for a room with air
   conditioning, but..........nope !!! Wasn't going to happen.
   UNBELEIVABLE !!! They offered no help. We had to pester them to get sum
   relief. Asked for a fan. They brought one, thankfully. Bottom line :
   this hotel's management IS NOT PROFESSIONAL, customer service is not a
   top priority. However, they do want YOU to make THEM a priority. It's
   the customers job to perform well....... At the breakfast buffet, if
   you stepped away from your table to get a refill, they would clear
   table and complain that too much food was being eaten. I DONT BLAME THE
   STAFF. It's the management that could have rectified the situation.
   They left the poor employees to deal with the angry customers. Many
   people complained. Left worker in tears. The other annoying issues :
   Wifi was super problematic. Had to go to front desk daily to get
   directions on what to do. Fridge didn't work. Empty Kleenex was not
   replaced. No lotions, only soap. BUT, funny thing is, you could
   "purchase" it from front desk. All in all, I WOULD NOT EVER, EVER, EVER
   STAY AT THIS HOTEL AGAIN !!!!! RECOMMENDATION : DON't even consider
   staying at Best Western Galice, Aix en Provence.

"Standard"

