"Retro hotel with good service"

   [blank.png] 3
   Laszlo G, 1114 Budapest
   08/08/2015

   This hotel is a really nice one, however a kinda budget one. All the
   rooms provide the retro feeling as you see the interior, even in tha
   bathroom as well. You may feel they try to modernize it but its just a
   try, still a long way to go.. Anyway service and kindness of staff is
   great, as it can be expected. Breakfast a good average, no more. The
   city center is also not so far, 15 min by walk. Trouser ironing machine
   is built in a room, I found it nice! :) WiFi is code based, valid for
   24 hours.

"mediocre"

   [blank.png] 3
   HHV, Amsterdam, The Netherlands
   04/08/2015

   This is a very average, somewhat bunker-like hotel, which caters – I
   suppose – mainly for groups. It is very large. I was promised a look at
   the garden or the swimming pool, and it is true that I could see the
   swimming pool far away, but what I really looked at was some sort of
   industrial aerea. The lamp next to my bed didn't function and there was
   (remarkably) only one other lamp in the room. The only reason to choose
   this hotel is because you can leave your car here without much problems
   and walk to the center of Aix in 20 minutes. The car park behind the
   hotel is public speace and the maximum tariff there is 9 euro's. I put
   my car there and had no problems. The garage of the hotel charges 12.
   The last morning of my stay I decided to take breakfast, but after I
   saw what I would pay 19 eur's for, I changed my mind. Personnel is
   friendly. Only good thing, the terrace at the swimming pool is nice and
   prices there are normal.

"Comfortable hotel with pool"

   [blank.png] 4
   born2bike, Ottawa, Canada
   19/07/2015

   We only stayed at this hotel one night, arriving by train and rolling
   our suitcases (do-able but a taxi might be a better choice). The room
   was quite large, with a very comfortable king-sized bed. We were
   delighted to discover that the hotel has an outdoor pool, although a
   little bemused at the 3 Euro charge for towels; as luck would have it,
   we had brought our own. The code-based wifi (a slip of paper with a
   long list of letters and numbers) is somewhat frustrating with the user
   having to re-enter the code before each session. The hotel is a 15
   minute walk to the center of Aix, with some restaurants located a
   little closer for those not wishing to make the trek into town. The
   hotel does have its own restaurant, which did not look too busy for a
   Saturday night. The front desk clerk was most helpful in ordering a
   taxi for the next morning, even going so far as to obtain pricing
   information and various options for us. Although it does not have the
   same flavor as a quaint provençal hotel, the Best Western is a good
   choice for those seeking value, space and comfort.

"Good Quality at Reasonable Price"

   [blank.png] 4
   User
   12/07/2015

   We had been travelling through Southern France and NW Italy and just
   needed a place to rest our head before the trek back up to Paris.
   Picked this place at random but it worked fine. Secure underground
   parking and check in was a breeze. Parts of the hotel seemed to be
   under renovation but our hall was fine. The room was huge and we
   actually got a real king bed which was nice after two weeks in small
   European beds. I suspect that the restaurant is usually better than it
   was that night as one of the waiters told us they were having staffing
   issues. This hotel isn't located at city centre but it is an easy walk.

"Needs to be updated"

   [blank.png] 3
   VALERIE880, Cambridge, United Kingdom
   21/06/2015

   My husband and I stayed at this hotel this June. It was situated a
   little out of Aix-en-Provence but still quiet. Not suitable for people
   with walking problems if they needed to walk into Aix for an evening
   meal. The breakfast was excellent even though the breakfast room was a
   little crowded at times. The rooms were a little tired and could do
   with some updating. The staff were all very friendly and helpful.

"adequate at west of city"

   [blank.png] 4
   Ivo P, Prague, Czech Republic
   02/10/2014

   It was my 3rd stay at BW hotels in France. It was at western side of
   city of Aix-en-Provence - typical BestWestern. :) The room was
   adequate, a bit outdate in colors, painting and laminate carpet shows
   signs of usage. The bed was very good. One electrical outlet in the
   room had a bad contact, sometimes it does not working properly.
   Internet wifi connection was quite useful even with several dropouts
   and variable bandwidth - according to inet occupation (rush hours) - I
   can not complain. I will come back eventualy.

